value.value: The process that is located along the ventral margin of the first valvula or the dorsal margin of the second valvula.
The sclerite that is located on wall of the salivarium and corresponds to the site of insertion of the ventral premento-salivarial muscle.

The anatomical space that is located on the boundary of the hypopharyngeal wall and the labium. The orifice is situated dorsally of the base of the glossa and corresponds to the opening for the salivarium.
The second abdominal sternal muscle that arises from the metadiscrimenal lamella.
The metacoxal muscle that arises from the second abdominal sternum.
The row that is composed of spurs.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of rod-like sensilla and is located apically on the distal labial palp segment.
The process that is located on the funicular segment.
The area that is located on the lateral wall of the first and second valvulae and is without annuli.
The pteralia that is located on the fore wing.
The projection that is located ventrally on the malar space.
The leg muscle that inserts on the protrochanter.
The row of spurs that extends along the apical margin of the fore tibia.
The spinasternum that is located anterior to the mesopectus.
The spine on the metapectal-propodeal complex that is paired and is medial to the propodeal spiracle.
The area on the propodeum that is median and is delimited laterally by the median longitudinal carina.
The muscle that inserts on the propleuron.
The propleural muscle that arises form the mesofurca.
The muscle that inserts on the prophragma.
The area that is delimted by two pronotal ridges laterally and the posterior margin of the pronotum anteriorly.
The carina that delimits the pronotal plate posterolaterally.
The apodeme that extends dorsally from the proximal part of the second valvula to the genital membrane and receives  the site of attachment of the posterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle.

The process that extends laterally from the proximal part of the second valvula and forms the median part of the basal articulation, and corresponds to the site of attachment for the anterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesopleuron.
The pleural sulcus that is located on the mesopleuron.
The anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle that originates from the mesopleuron and inserts on the mesothoracic spiracle.
The spinasternum that is located between the mesopectus and metapectus.
The row of spurs that extends laterally along the tarsomere of the mesotarsus.
The area that is located ventrally of the mesopectus and limited dorsally by any line.
The row of spurs that extends along the distal margin of the mesotibia.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metabasalare.
The leg muscle that inserts on the metacoxa.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metafurca.
The area that is located laterally on the metaphragma.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metalaterophragma.
The carina that is transverse and is located on the metascutellum.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metanotum.
The metatrochantinal muscle that arises form the metanotum.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metaphragma.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metapleuron.
The metasomal spiracle that is located on the metasomal tergum 7.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metasubalare.
The leg muscle that inserts on the metatrochanter.
The trochantin that is located in the metathorax.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metatrochantin.
The edge that is located on the cranium along the oral foramen.
The projection that is located distomedially on the hypopygium.
The multiporous plate sensillum that is gustatory in function.
The multiporous plate sensillum that is olfactory in function.
The patch that is elevated, located on the flagellomere and is multiporous.
